  "texts": [
    "It so far has no counter-examples.",
    "The same is true of some strings of formal symbols like \"2 + 2 = 4,\" which are, like sentences, interpretable as propositions, with subjects, predicates and truth-values.",
    "In fact, the propositions of mathematics are probably best thought of as a subset or part of natural language, with meanings (i.e., semantics) in the (grounded) heads of their human users.",
    "But in the Turing Machine doing the symbol manipulations, there are neither referents nor meanings; just shape-based rules, which are purely syntactic.",
    "Now, a question: Why are the symbols in mathematics and the words in natural language non-iconic?"
  ],
